Sadtu called on the Gauteng Education Department to take the safety and security of teachers and pupils at schools seriously after the stabbing. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Democratic Teachers Union (Sadtu) has called on the Gauteng Education Department to take the safety and security of teachers and pupils at schools seriously after the stabbing of a principal in Soweto.Nothemba Lebepe was stabbed multiple times in full view of pupils at the Paul Mosaka Primary School in Pimville on Monday, allegedly by a former teacher. The teacher resigned last year after claims that he lied about his qualifications.Sadtu s Tseliso Ledimo said: We strongly condemn it because we have been raising issues of safety and security in schools. But this matter must be given closer and attention. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)